<br>
I believe I should live my life by my morals, but I don't necessarily think that gives me the right to impose my morals on anyone else.  I guess the society i'm a part of has the right to have a collective morality (its &quot;laws&quot;), and because I choose to be a part of the society, I accept its &quot;morals&quot;.  If I were held in this society against my will, that'd be wrong.  If my society decided to impose its morals on another society, that'd be wrong.  However, it's &quot;majority rule&quot; in human societies - when its 10 societies versus one, the 10 will win, so at that point you're talking global morality.<br>
<br>
Whatever, it gets confusing to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Anyway back to my original point - yes, I call him evil.  That doesn't mean I think I am personally responsible for removing him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elcheproudfoot>Elche Proudfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mmmmm lobster</span><br>  Posts: 1122<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/10/03 2:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=297>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.woc.org/public/oneirodynia/images/srllogo.GIF height=180 width=180></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Morality is not relative.&quot;</span><hr size=1> How can evil exist when there is nothing by which to judge it against? One man's Evil is another man's  Good.<br>
