<br>
I would agree that morality is relative if all we had to go on was the ideas of other men.  Humans are infinitely fallible, after all.  That is why, way back when this all started, I stated that my arguments would only make any sense at all if one believed in some sort of Higher Power.<br>
<br>
The fact that all men are fallible (which you may or may not agree with, but which makes sense in a relativistic world) also ties in with Wolvar's argument.  You say that because we can't ever know for absolutely sure that our interpretations or knowledge of the Truth is right, we never have any justification for imposing our beliefs on others.  To this I would respond with, first of all, that this believe would result in complete moral paralysis - if we can't do anything until we're 100% sure, nothing would ever get done.  Just like with any decision making process, you evaluate the facts and make your best decision.  Depending on the scope of your proposed action, a smaller or larger margin of error will be acceptable.  In a situation like the war on Iraq, we'd better be pretty close to sure that we're right, after all.  However, another mitigating factor is the imperative of self protection which I've already gone over.  You have to look at not only the cost of acting (especially considering the consequences of you being wrong), but the cost of NOT acting.<br>
<br>
and...<br>
<br>
Mankind was not made as sinners.  There was this little business called &quot;The Fall&quot;, you know.  If you want to argue that it was unfair to condemn all mankind for the disobedience of two people, that's another thing (to which I would respond that salvation is also offered to all mankind...) <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A> at: 3/10/03 5:11:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mertondraco>Merton Draco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fuck all of you</span><br>  Posts: 2180<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/10/03 5:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=303>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The moral code (broadly speaking) and the political values and culture of the United States of America have produced the most prosperous, free nation on the face of the planet.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
